IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: TO ELIMINATE POVERTY & COMBAT EXISTING POVERTY.
IRS990.MissionDesc: THE MISSION OF PROJECT NOW, INC. IS TO STRENGTHEN COMMUNITIES BY HELPING PEOPLE HELP THEMSELVES AND ONE ANOTHER. WE ENVISION THE WHOLE COMMUNITY WORKING HAND IN HAND TO MEET HUMAN NEEDS, PROTECT HUMAN DIGNITY AND RESTORE HOPE.
IRS990.Desc: WEATHERIZATION/ENERGY ASSISTANCE:PROJECT NOW PROVIDES WEATHERIZATION AND ENERGY ASSISTANCE TO HELP REDUCE HEATING AND COOLING COSTS FOR LOW-INCOME RESIDENTS OF ROCK ISLAND, MERCER AND HENRY COUNTIES. ENERGY ASSISTANCE AND WEATHERIZATION PROGRAMS PROVIDED ASSISTANCE TO 12,674 CUSTOMERS IN 5,930 HOMES DURING THE YEAR. FUNDING FOR THESE PROGRAMS IS THROUGH FEDERAL AND STATE GRANTS AND LOCAL ENERGY COMPANIES.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: CHILD EDUCATION:PROJECT NOW HEAD START PROMOTES THE SCHOOL READINESS OF PRESCHOOL-AGED CHILDREN FROM LOW-INCOME FAMILIES WHILE PROVIDING COMPREHENSIVE SERVICES TO THE FAMILIES. HEAD START OFFERS A VARIETY OF SERVICES THAT SUPPORT THE CHILDREN, INCLUDING THOSE WITH SPECIAL NEEDS OR DISABILITIES, IN A POSITIVE LEARNING ENVIRONMENT. THE FUNDED ENROLLMENT IS 330 CHILDREN IN BOTH CENTER AND HOME-BASED PROGRAMS. FUNDING IS PROVIDED THROUGH THE US DEPARTMENT OF HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: COMMUNITY SERVICE:PROVIDES APPLICATION ASSISTANCE, SUPPORT, ADVOCACY AND INFORMATION & REFERRAL TO RESIDENTS OF ROCK ISLAND, HENRY AND MERCER COUNTIES. CUSTOMERS ARE HELPED TO MANAGE THEIR BASIC NEEDS WHILE THEY MOVE TOWARDS INCREASED SELF-SUFFICIENCY. RENT & DEPOSIT ASSISTANCE TO 1,159 HOUSEHOLDS. COORDINATED ENTRY HELPED 602 FAMILIES WITH HOUSING AND CASE MANAGEMENT. FUNDING IS PROVIDED THROUGH FEDERAL, STATE AND LOCAL GRANTS.

ProgSrvcAccomActyOtherGrp.Desc: SENIOR PROGRAMS:DESIGNED TO HELP SENIORS LIVE INDEPENDENTLY IN THEIR OWN HOMES. SERVICES INCLUDE: HOME-DELIVERED MEALS, CONGREGATE MEALS, TRANSPORTATION, INFORMATION AND ASSISTANCE, AND OUTREACH SERVICES. 112,127 HOME DELIVERED MEALS WERE SERVED TO 1,131 SENIORS. 19,023 MEALS WERE SERVED TO 423 SENIORS WHO WERE ELIGIBLE FOR CONGREGATE SERVICES. 5,331 UNITS OF DOOR-TO-DOOR TRANSPORTATION WERE PROVIDED TO 202 SENIORS IN ROCK ISLAND AND MERCER COUNTIES. 2,580 SENIORS RECEIVED INFORMATION AND ASSISTANCE AND 240 FARMER MARKET COUPON BOOKS WORTH $6,000 WERE DISTRIBUTED TO SENIORS. 31 MEDICARE BENEFICIARIES WERE SAVED AN ESTIMATE OF $34,858 FOR THE YEAR.

HOUSING AND HOUSING REHABILITATION:PROJECT NOW PROVIDES HOUSING SERVICES INCLUDING HOME REHABILITATION (SINGLE FAMILY REHAB AND HOUSING ACCESSIBILITY PROGRAMS) TO LOW INCOME INDIVIDUALS OF ROCK ISLAND, MERCER AND HENRY COUNTIES. FUNDING IS PROVIDED THROUGH THE ILLINOIS HOUSING DEVELOPMENT AUTHORITY (IHDA); 23 HOMES WERE COMPLETED DURING 2017-2019 WITH 8 BEING COMPLETED IN THE 2018/2019 YEAR. COMPLETED 9 HOMES DURING 2019-2020. COMPLETED 6 HOMES DURING 2020-2021 YEAR. PROJECT NOW ALSO HAS 102 AFFORDABLE RENTAL PROPERTIES 11 OF THEM ARE COMMERCIAL.
PUBLIC TRANSIT: PROJECT NOW IS THE SERVICE PROVIDER FOR RIM RURAL PUBLIC TRANSIT SERVING RURAL ROCK ISLAND AND ALL OF MERCER COUNTIES. 230 PASSENGERS RECEIVED 10,379 RIDES THIS YEAR.
FOOD PROGRAMS:DESIGNED TO FEED LOW INCOME INDIVIDUALS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATIONS ARE REQUIRED TO ASSESS WHETHER IT IS MORE LIKELY THAN NOT THAT A TAX POSITION WILL BE SUSTAINED UPON EXAMINATION ON THE TECHNICAL MERITS OF THE POSITION, ASSUMING THE TAXING AUTHORITY HAS FULL KNOWLEDGE OF ALL INFORMATION. IF THE TAX POSITION DOES NOT MEET THE MORE-LIKELY-THAN-NOT RECOGNITION THRESHOLD, THE BENEFIT OF THAT POSITION IS NOT RECOGNIZED IN THE CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. THE ORGANIZATIONS HAVE DETERMINED THERE ARE NO AMOUNTS TO RECORD AS ASSETS OR LIABILITIES RELATED TO UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS.
THE ORGANIZATION MONITORS THE USE OF GRANT FUNDS THROUGH COMPLIANCE WITH FUNDING SOURCE REQUIREMENTS.
THE ORGANIZATION REPORTS THE ACTUAL NUMBER OF CONTRIBUTORS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FORM 990 IS REVIEWED THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR AND FINANCE DIRECTOR. THE FINANCE COMMITTEE APPROVES THE FORM 990 AND THE BOARD IS PROVIDED A COPY OF THE FORM 990 PRIOR TO IT BEING FILED WITH THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: NO MEMBER OF THE BOARD SHALL CAST A VOTE ON ANY MATTER WHICH HAS A DIRECT BEARING ON SERVICES TO BE PROVIDED BY THE MEMBER OR ANY ORGANIZATION FROM WHICH SUCH MEMBER DIRECTLY FINANCIALLY BENEFITS OR WHICH THEY REPRESENT. NO PERSON MAY SIT ON THE BOARD WHO IS AN OFFICER OR EMPLOYEE OF ANY ORGANIZATION CONTRACTING TO PERFORM WORK FUNDED BY THE CORPORATION OR FUNDED THROUGH THE ORGANIZATION. A MEMBER OF THE BOARD, WHO HOLDS A DIRECT OR INDIRECT FINANCIAL INTEREST IN (OR WILL RECEIVE A BENEFIT FROM) THE GRANTING OF FUNDS TO AN ENTITY OR INDIVIDUAL SHALL DISCLOSE SUCH TRANSACTION TO THE BOARD. THE MEMBER SHALL IDENTIFY ANY CONFLICT OF INTEREST, INCLUDING CONFLICTS OF ANY CONSIDERATION OF THE MATTER BY THE BOARD OR ANY BOARD COMMITTEE. THE BOARD WILL DETERMINE IF A CONFLICT EXISTS AND DETERMINE APPROPRIATE ACTION. IF ANY QUESTION IS RAISED AS TO WHETHER A CONFLICT OF INTEREST EXISTS, THE POTENTIALLY INTERESTED BOARD MEMBER SHALL LEAVE THE MEETING WHILE THE MATTER IS DISCUSSED AND VOTED UPON. THE REMAINING MEMBERS SHALL DECIDE IF A CONFLICT OF INTEREST EXISTS. ANY VOTE APPROVING THE TRANSACTION THAT INVOLVES A POSSIBLE CONFLICT OF INTEREST, SHOULD INCLUDE A DETERMINATION BY THE DISINTERESTED DIRECTORS THAT THE TRANSACTION IS IN THE BEST INTEREST OF THE CORPORATION AND IS FAIR IN ALL RESPECTS TO THE CORPORATION. THE MINUTES OF THE MEETING SHALL REFLECT THAT A DISCLOSURE WAS MADE AND THE NATURE OF THE DISCLOSURE, THAT THE INTERESTED DIRECTOR ABSTAINED FROM VOTING AND LEFT THE ROOM FOR THE FINAL DISCUSSION AND VOTE, AND THAT THE INTERESTED DIRECTOR ABSTAINED FROM THE ACTION TAKEN TO DETERMINE WHETHER A CONFLICT OF INTEREST EXISTED, IF ANY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: DETERMINATION OF COMPENSATION INCLUDES A YEARLY REVIEW, COMPENSATION SURVEY OR STUDY OF SIMILAR POSITIONS IN SIMILAR ORGANIZATIONS AND APPROVAL BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST.
